window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>I was supposed to help him find his soulmate—not fall for him myself.</p> <p>I’m Indie Valentine: cupid by trade, sarcasm specialist by nature, and currently one step away from a matchmaking meltdown. For the past year, I’ve been assigned to Mesmer—a stoic, endearingly sweet gargoyle who’s spent his whole life waiting for his mate.</p> <p>The problem? I can’t seem to find her anywhere.</p> <p>He’s patient. Kind. An alpha in that quiet, protective way that makes your heart flutter and your knees forget how to function. And the longer I’m around him, the more I start to wonder if someone, somewhere, got their wires crossed—because I feel the pull. I see him. And I want more than I should.</p> <p>Facing danger and foiling assassination plots?</p> <p>Totally normal.</p> <p>Falling for my client?</p> <p>Not part of the plan.</p> <p>Still…some connections are written in the stars, no matter how hard you try to resist them.</p>"; 
